{"cursor":"20023","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n'Weed control' is the botanical component of pest control, using physical and\nchemical methods to stop weeds from reaching a mature stage of growth when they\ncould be harmful to domesticated plants and livestock. In order to reduce weed\ngrowth, many \"weed control\" strategies have been developed in order to contain\nthe growth and spread of weeds.\n\nThe most basic is ploughing which cuts the roots of annual weeds. Today,\nchemical weed killers known as herbicides are widely used.\n","linknr":423,"url":"Weed_control","recorded":1362503853,"links":31,"instances":["plant","plant","tool","gardening"],"pdf":["http://www.soil-steaming-steam-boiler-blog.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/10/steaming-research-results_dlr2010.pdf"],"categories":["Horticultural techniques","Agronomy","Pest control"],"headings":["Exact definition","Effects on other plants","Methods","UK legislation","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/91/Maler_der_Grabkammer_des_Sennudem_001.jpg/220px-Maler_der_Grabkammer_des_Sennudem_001.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Farmer_plowing_in_Fahrenwalde%2C_Mecklenburg-Vorpommern%2C_Germany.jpg/32px-Farmer_plowing_in_Fahrenwalde%2C_Mecklenburg-Vorpommern%2C_Germany.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Speicherkoog_Kartoffelacker_Abflammger%C3%A4t_Envo-Dan.jpg/220px-Speicherkoog_Kartoffelacker_Abflammger%C3%A4t_Envo-Dan.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/be/Weeding.jpg/220px-Weeding.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/08/Dwarswieder.jpg/220px-Dwarswieder.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo